STATEMENT OF OPERATING CONDITIONS MIDCOAST PIPELINES (EAST TEXAS) L.P.
Subject to the conditions and terms provided herein, Midcoast Pipelines (East Texas) L.P., hereinafter "Midcoast", will provide firm and interruptible transportation service on its intrastate pipeline facilities in the State of Texas under Section 311(a)(2) of the Natural Gas Policy Act of 1978 ("NGPA") "on behalf of" (1) a local distribution company served by an interstate pipeline; or (2) an interstate pipeline company.
1. Such transportation will only be provided pursuant to a written agreement with Midcoast (i) executed by the party on whose behalf the transportation is performed; or (ii) executed by any other party as long as Midcoast is provided proof that in Midcoast's sole judgment is sufficient to show that the transportation service is performed "on behalf of" an interstate pipeline or a local distribution company served by an interstate pipeline.
2. Any shipper which contracts for transportation service will be required to (i) warrant in the transportation agreement that Midcoast's transportation is "on behalf of" an interstate pipeline or a local distribution company served by an interstate pipeline company and (ii) hold Midcoast harmless for any breach of said warranty.
3. Such transportation will be performed by Midcoast only at the maximum rate authorized by Section 311(a)(2) of the NGPA and Commission's regulation thereunder unless Midcoast chooses in its sole discretion to charge a lower rate. Midcoast's decision to charge a lower rate than the maximum authorized rate for any particular transportation arrangement shall not entitle any shipper to receive service at the lower rate for any other transportation arrangement.
4. Such transportation will be fully interruptible if, in Midcoast's sole judgment, its pipeline capacity is needed to provide service to:
i. Any customer entitled to receive firm sales or firm transportation service;
ii. Any sales customer;
iii. Any interruptible transportation customer willing to pay a higher rate for interruptible transportation service; or
iv. Any interruptible transportation customer who requested and contracted for interruptible service at the same rate at an earlier time.
5. Such transportation service shall be subject to the terms of Appendix "A" governing Delivery Pressure.
6. Any gas transported must meet the quality specification of appendix "B" and is subject to the conditions thereof.
7. Shipper shall agree to reimburse Midcoast, upon billing, for any and all fees for reports filed or authorization sought in conjunction with such service.
8. Midcoast shall not be required to perform such transportation unless the shipper meets the financial viability standards of Appendix "C".
APPENDIX A
DELIVERY PRESSURES
1. Subject to Paragraph 3, all gas delivered by or for the account of Shipper of Midcoast shall be delivered at pressures sufficient to enter Midcoast's pipeline system against the working pressures maintained therein from time to time.
2. Subject to Paragraph 3, all gas delivered by Midcoast to Shipper or Shipper's designee shall be delivered at pressures existing in Midcoast's pipeline system from time to time.
3. Neither Midcoast or Shipper shall be obligated to compress gas in order to effect delivery thereof to the other party, nor shall either party or its designee be obligated to receive gas at pressures exceeding the maximum allowable operating pressures of their respective facilities as prescribed under any applicable governmental regulations.
APPENDIX B
QUALITY
All gas tendered for transportation shall be merchantable natural gas and shall meet all the following Quality Specifications:
a. Hydrogen Sulphide: The gas shall not contain more than one quarter (1/4) grain of hydrogen sulphide per hundred (100) cubic feet as determined by a method generally acceptable for use in the gas industry.
b. Total Sulphur: The gas shall not contain more than four (4) grains of total Sulphur per hundred (100) cubic feet of gas as determined by a method generally acceptable for use in the gas industry.
c. Temperature: The gas shall not have a temperature of less than forty degrees (40?) nor more than one hundred twenty degrees (120?) Fahrenheit.
d. Carbon Dioxide: The gas shall not contain in excess of two percent (2%) by volume of carbon dioxide.
e. Total Inerts: The gas shall not contain in excess of four percent (4%) by volume of carbon dioxide plus nitrogen.
f. Oxygen: The gas shall not contain in excess of two-tenths of one percent (0.2%) by volume of oxygen.
g. Objectionable Liquids and Solids: The gas shall be free of objectionable liquids and solids and other potentially harmful matter and be commercially free from dust, gums gum-forming constituents or other liquid or solid matter which might become separated from gas in the course of transportation through pipelines.
h. Heating Value: The gas shall not have a Heating Value of less than nine hundred seventy-five (975) Btu's per cubic foot.
i. Water: The gas shall in no event have in excess of seven (7) pounds of water vapor per million (1,000,000) cubic feet of gas.
j. Mercaptans: The mercaptan content shall not exceed five parts per million (5ppm) by volume.
APPENDIX C
FINANCIAL VIABILITY OF SHIPPER
Midcoast shall not be required to perform or continue to perform service on behalf of any Shipper that has applied for bankruptcy under Chapter 11 of the Bankruptcy Code or on behalf of any Shipper who fails to make any payment to Midcoast fully and promptly when due or on behalf of any Shipper who, in Midcoast's sole judgment, fails to demonstrate creditworthiness; provided, however, such Shipper may receive service if said Shipper prepays for such service, or upon fifteen (15) days notice from Transporter, furnishes good and sufficient surety bond or other good and sufficient security, as determined by Midcoast in its sole discretion, of a continuing nature, and in an amount equal to the cost of performing the transportation service requested by or provided to Shipper for a four (4) month period.
